<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={7.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={15.56}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={16.50}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={7.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={15.56}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={16.50}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>25</li><li>69.97</li><li>85.32</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}^{{2}}={15.56}^{{2}}+{16.5}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({15.56}\right)}{\left({16.5}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{49}={242.1136}+{272.25}-{513.48}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{465.3636}=-{513.48}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.90629352652489}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={25.001933275594}={25}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({25.001933275594}\right)}}}}{{7.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{15.56}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.28993889546888}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left(-{0.28993889546888}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={69.96574932984}\approx{69.97}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25.001933275594}+{69.96574932984}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={85.315976183746}\approx{85.32}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

